</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft"> <a href="/blog/poetry/bilingual-poem-gaza-refaat-alareer" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Alareer-Anchor.jpg?itok=7JDsu0FR" width="100" height="75" alt="A black and white illustration of a hand emerging from the ground with a string tied to one extended finger that leads to a kite in the sky above" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />
</a>
</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/poetry/bilingual-poem-gaza-refaat-alareer">A Bilingual Poem from Gaza
</a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">Illustration by fran_kie / Adobe StockIf I Must Die
If I must die,
you must live
to tell my story
to sell my things
to buy a piece of cloth
and some…
